 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvestas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vestas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/22/01 9:28:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2096.topic&index=76>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wow</span><hr size=1> I played in karnors for 5 hours last night and quite honestly I noticed very little change. I'm wielding a ragebringer primary and a jagged ice shard secondary.  Not super uber, but not something to pass over either.  The warriors in the group were a 55 with epics and a 52nd without.<br>
<br>
I &quot;may&quot; have aggro'd a few more times than normal but honestly, nothing conclusive to point a finger at.  Pre-patch I always made a point of pre-evading, post patch I still do and this seems to be the way to go.  I only noticed real aggro issues if I attacked first and didn't evade for some time.<br>
<br>
Likewise the two different clerics we had over the night both used celestial and complete healing and quite honestly, I noticed very little increase in the amount of aggro they go.  As usual, having to heal early gave the clerics grief and, in multi-mob situations (no chanter) casting a complete heal would aggro the mobs we hadn't touched yet.  But it was nothing we couldn't handle.<br>
<br>
I haven't seen the affects on a large raid, but, Nightmare's Asylum took down Trak last night in under 30seconds of fighting and reported no real problems.<br>
<br>
Methinks folks are over reacting to what was some minor tweaking done by Verant and exaggerating a few things. I'm sure clerics will aggro a bit more now (and if the patch message is correct then they should) and a few more rogues will take a bit more damage.  But we're not talking about anything that is so threatening to the game as to re-write or destroy it completely. <p><img src = "http://www.geocities.com/maxfields_2000/sunglassvest1.jpg" >

